N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 7846.1 - Notices, briefs, appeals and other documents

State Regulations

Documents shall be filed electronically unless the filing
party certifies that it is unable to do so, in which case a paper document may
be filed. When a document is served by a party on another party, service shall
be by electronic means unless the serving and receiving parties agree
otherwise, or the secretary or hearing officer authorizes the use of a
different means of service. Notes
